UDEL - udel.GardenProject.enums.PlantDataSource
Plant data originated from the University of Delaware Flora Database.
udel.GardenProject.enums - package udel.GardenProject.enums
All the different enums for the Garden Project.
udel.GardenProject.garden - package udel.GardenProject.garden
All the critical code that brings the application together and runs it.
udel.GardenProject.plants - package udel.GardenProject.plants
Contains the Plant class that stores all the information that can be obtained by the PlantLoader, and Comparators to sort the a list of Plant objects for searching.
udel.GardenProject.plotObjects - package udel.GardenProject.plotObjects
Contains all the plot objects that can be placed on the Plot Designer.

Placed within the main.udel.plants package as plants can also be placed on the Plot Designer.

Has Buildings, Fences, Rivers, and other critical plot objects.

NOTE: Everything in this package needs to implement the Serializable interface to be serialized by Model's save method when acting on the Session class.

NOTE 2: Every class in this package and any subpackages must implement PlotObject or implement an abstract class that itself implements PlotObject at some point.
udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.lines - package udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.lines
 
udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.polygons - package udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.polygons
Polygons can have an arbitrary number of points, have points that are editable, points that move with the polygon as the polygon is dragged, and other critical polygon features.

All classes in this package should extend the GenericPolygon abstract class and give it an AdjustablePolygon, specifying its color, anchor color, and more.
udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.special - package udel.GardenProject.plotObjects.special
All the special PlotObjects that don't fit neatly into the other categories.
udel.GardenProject.windows - package udel.GardenProject.windows
All the distinct windows that can be displayed to the user.
UNDERSTORY - udel.GardenProject.enums.Canopy
